    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-29T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-29T12:00:00-05:00" n="110"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1"
                    >EW</gloss>/6–2945: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 110 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d110fn1">Sent to the Secretary of State ad interim over the
                        signature of <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-29T20:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 29, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2325. <gloss target="#t_topsec1">Top sec</gloss> from <persName corresp="#p_PEW1"
                        >Pauley</persName> to the President.</p>
                <p>I am bending every effort to have a proposed reparation plan to submit to you and
                    the heads of Great Brit and <persName corresp="#p_R4">Russia</persName> at your
                    forth-coming <pb facs="0267" n="135" xml:id="pg_135"/> meeting. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MIM1">Maisky</persName> representing USSR and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MSW1">Monckton</persName> representing <gloss target="#t_UK1"
                        >UK</gloss> expect to be at such meeting and naturally I hope to be there as
                    per my conversation with you before leaving US. Accordingly I would appreciate
                    your notifying the Army and having the Army advise me of arrangements to attend
                    this conference for myself, Dr. <persName corresp="#p_LI1">Lubin</persName> and
                    four others. Best regards.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
